caption: You say ‘flood’ like it’s a bad thing.
This must be your first flood.
Wait, there’s a flood coming, and you want us to get IN the boat?
You took us out of school for this?
Being on cedar planks makes us really uncomfortable.
Which list are we on, guest or menu?
We’ll meet you there.
Let me guess - the cats suggested you bring us.
I think we’ll take our chances.”
Really?  Do you do everything He tells you?
What do you mean we'd be useful on Fridays?
All this so you can spread our descendants on bagels?
We were told that there would be water.
We weren't endangered until a few minutes ago.
Trust us, we'll be fine out here. And after few days, you're really not going to want us in there.
You do know that trying to rescue us from a huge body of water is kind of weird, right?
How about we skip the ark and just meet up with you at Mount Ararat in a few weeks.
We’ll take our chances with the flood if that’s alright with you
Yes, we're sushi grade. Why do you ask?
The cats invited us.
Psalmon 8:8
Can you give us a hand?  We're floundering here.
We would like a cabin with an open porthole.
Forty days of floods? Are you kidding, Noah? That's our wet dream.
We left a few thousand eggs in steerage
I know what God said, but I think we'll be OK.
Don’t tell me you already have two talking fish.
C’mon,man. Fish gotta swim.
What, you thought we'd drown?
Bears and eagles also? You know what, I'll take my chances at home.
